Meet Our Team





Management Team





Larry Gerdes
CEO & Executive Chairman
of Pursuant Health

Show Biography
Larry Gerdes, CEO & Executive Chairman of Pursuant Health, Mr. Gerdes has served as CEO of Pursuant Health (Formerly SoloHealth), a private health-care company in Atlanta, since February, 2014, and as its Executive Chairman of the Board since November 2013 and as its Chairman since 2012. Since 1983, Mr. Gerdes has also served as a general partner of Sand Hill Financial Company, a venture capital partnership. Mr. Gerdes is a general partner of Gerdes Huff Investments and a major shareholder and President of Friesland Farms, LLC . Mr. Gerdes formerly served as Chairman and CEO of Transcend Services, concluding with the sale of that company in April 2012 and as a director of Access Plans, Inc., from 2001 until its sale in June, 2012. Mr. Gerdes previously served as Chairman of the board of Pursuant Health (Formerly SoloHealth) and on the board of CBOT Holdings. Mr. Gerdes is a member of the Dean’s Advisory Council for The Kelley School of Business at Indiana University and serves as trustee for Monmouth College.






Joe Stephens
Chief Financial Officer
of Pursuant Health

Show Biography
Joe Stephens, Chief Financial Officer of Pursuant Health, started with Pursuant Health (Formerly SoloHealth) in March, 2013. In his role with the Company, Stephens oversees the finance, accounting and fundraising activities. During his time with the Company, Stephens has managed sales, implementations, delivery and reporting, and implemented many processes to streamline and improve the efficiency of these organizations.
Prior to Pursuant Health, Stephens was VP of Process Improvement at Nuance Communications, where he created scorecards to measure and maintain field operations, managed 12 overseas vendor relationships and drove operational efficiencies through process improvement initiatives. He also spent time in sales at Tractor & Equipment Company, where he developed a new business unit within the organizational framework of the larger company.
Stephens was recognized as the top salesman in the country for Komatsu Utility in 2006 and holds an MBA from the Kelley School of Business, with a concentration in finance and marketing. In his time away from Pursuant Health, Stephens enjoys investing in the stock market, learning about sustainable energy and spending time at the beach. Stephens also was a member of the varsity football team at Auburn University.






Ryan Sloan
Chief Marketing Officer
of Pursuant Health

Show Biography
Ryan Sloan, Chief Marketing Officer of Pursuant Health, oversees consumer marketing, product strategy, partnerships, and new business ventures for Pursuant Health.
Prior to his time at Pursuant Health, Ryan spent 12 years with Aetna in Corporate Strategy, Sales and P&L Management. He led a high profile division to exceed an aggressive 2012 Sales Plan by 40%, accounting for one third of Aetna’s growth that year. He worked closely with leaders from premier health systems and medical groups across the country to develop and execute go-to-market strategies for launch of 12 joint-products. He was also in charge of special projects including Aetna’s Health Care Reform implementation and strategic business planning post-Reform for the Mid America region.
Ryan holds a BA in Economics from the University of Georgia and an MBA from the Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University. He enjoys spending time outdoors and with his family, and is a legal citizen of three countries – the United States, Canada and the United Kingdom.






Robert Lort
VP of Kiosk Network Operations
of Pursuant Health

Show Biography
Robert Lort, VP of Kiosk Network Operations of Pursuant Health, oversees the production, deployment and support of the Pursuant Health kiosks. Since 2011 when Lort joined the company, the number of kiosks in market has vastly increased – going from less than 100 kiosks deployed nationwide to over 3,500. Lort successfully deployed those machines and scaled the company’s support team during that short period. He has also been an instrumental figure in developing partnerships with companies such as Dell and NCR.
Prior to his time with Pursuant Health, Lort was responsible for the deployment of Horizon Software’s POS systems in various vertical markets including major hospital systems, colleges and universities, retirement facilities and private schools across the country. Professional organizations he is tied to include Technology Association of Georgia (TAG) and Operations Managers of America.
In his time away from Pursuant Health, Lort enjoys watching his two sons play baseball and basketball, keeping up with the latest trends in technology and playing the drums.






Kathryn Laughlin,
VP of Product & Implementations
of Pursuant Health

Show Biography
Kathryn Laughlin, VP of Product & Implementations of Pursuant Health, oversees the implementation and account management of employer wellness programs. Laughlin works closely with employers to properly scope the project and lead the project management efforts to deliver a successful and highly engaging program. After joining the team in 2011, she led multiple projects including the deployment of 3,500 kiosks in retail locations, all kiosk logistics, trade show installations, software integrations with 3rd parties and lead generation software implementations for health plans.
Prior to Pursuant Health, Laughlin was a project manager for the Vertical Market team at Horizon Software leading POS installations in hospitals, colleges and universities, retirement facilities and large institutions, such as The Federal Reserve Bank. She also managed HL7 integration projects for hospitals throughout the country. After years of project management experience, she was able to complete her Project Management Professional (PMP) certification in 2012.
Laughlin is currently pursuing an MBA at The University of Georgia. When she is away from Pursuant Health, she enjoys taking piano lessons, golfing, cycling and traveling with her husband.






Scott Robertson,
Chief Technology Officer
of Pursuant Health

Show Biography
Scott Robertson, Chief Technology Officer, is responsible for overseeing  Product Development, Infrastructure, Data & Integration, Technical Operations, Technical Support, Ad Operations, Customer Service and Regulatory & Compliance for Pursuant Health.
Prior to joining Pursuant Health, Scott spent 16 years with Transcend Services building and managing their software technology platforms, product management, infrastructure and technology operations teams and HIPAA & SOX compliance programs.  He managed teams that were geographically dispersed across the United States as well as internationally.  Scott helped lead Transcend through multiple acquisitions and the complex technology and platform integrations that followed.  The success of Transcend ultimately resulted in it’s acquisition by Nuance Communications in 2012 for $300MM.  Post acquisition, Scott spent the following two years leading five separate software engineering teams for their mid-market platforms that were responsible for contributing over 200MM in annual revenue.
Scott has a BS in Geology and a MS in Geochemistry from Georgia State University.






Jeff Marwill,
Vice President of Sales
for Pursuant Health

Show Biography
Jeff Marwill, Vice President of Sales,
is responsible for sales strategy and revenue growth for Pursuant Health.  Prior to his time at Pursuant Health, Jeff was a Client Outcomes Executive for Nuance Communications.  In this role, Jeff was responsible for growing revenue across multiple product and service lines and managing strategic relationships with some of the largest U.S. healthcare customers.  Jeff has also held operational roles with responsibility for US and Asia Operations as well as technology roles with responsibility for systems management and software development efforts.
 Jeff holds a Master’s of Science in Health Informatics from The University of Alabama at Birmingham and a BA from The University of Texas at Austin.  Jeff enjoys outdoor activities with his family including coaching and playing soccer, waterskiing, wakeboarding and other water sports.






