Stanley Blaylock
Board Member of
Pursuant Health
Show Biography
Stanley Blaylock‚ Board Member of Pursuant Health, began his career in health care investment banking, ultimately rising to the role of Global Co-Head of Health Care Investment Banking at (Deutsche Bank Alex. Brown). He then co-founded specialty pharmacy solutions company Medmark, where he served as its EVP, CFO and CAO until his promotion to President and CEO in 2005.   When Walgreens acquired Medmark in 2006, Blaylock joined the company, and went on to become Walgreens SVP and President of Walgreens Health Services.  Blaylock currently serves as the President and CEO of Physicians Immediate Care, a leading urgent care company in the Midwest. Blaylock holds a degree in economics and communication studies from the University of Virginia and an MBA from Harvard Business School. Blaylock is also a Fellow of the CEO Perspective Program from Northwestern’s Kellogg School of Management and Corporate Leadership Center. 




Sonia Jain
