Pursuant Health
Show Biography
Sonia Jain, Board Member of Pursuant Health, joined Outerwall in 2010 and assumed the role of VP Finance & Treasurer, overseeing treasury and mergers and acquisitions, in 2012. Prior to joining Outerwall, Sonia was an investment banker at Morgan Stanley, focusing on the Consumer and Retail sectors, and a consultant with McKinsey & Company. She is currently a board member of Pursuant Health. Sonia graduated magna cum laude from Princeton University with a degree in Electrical Engineering and also received an MS in Electrical Engineering from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and an MBA from Harvard Business School.





Peter A. Krivkovich
Board Member of
Pursuant Health
Show Biography
Peter A. Krivkovich, Board Member of Pursuant Health,  is a founding member of AdRoll, an online advertising company, where he oversees the company’s finance, sales and operations.
Prior to AdRoll, Krivkovich served in leadership roles spanning, finance, business development, product management and sales. He spent two years in investment banking at ABN AMRO doing M&A and was in business development and then product management at Everdream Corporation. Krivkovich also helped oversee Good Technology’s 100-person sales team, before moving into a finance role with the company.
Krivkovich holds a BA in Economics from Emory University, an MBA from Harvard Business School and studied economics at the London School of Economics.





John Jesser
Board Member of
Pursuant Health
Show Biography
John Jesser, Board Member of Pursuant Health,  serves as the vice president of Provider Engagement Strategy for WellPoint, Inc., the nation’s largest health benefits company. In this capacity, Mr. Jesser manages a company wide process that looks at healthcare-related functions to improve the affordability of health care; the consumer experience and access to care. He leads the company’s telehealth strategy as the general manager of LiveHealth Online, an online care solution for consumers and providers being offered to Anthem’s customers. Mr. Jesser focuses on solutions and digital tools that improve the connection between doctors, hospitals, consumers and health plans. Previously, Mr. Jesser served for more than 24 years in various management positions within the health care field.
Mr. Jesser earned his Bachelor or Science degree in mass communications from Miami University in Oxford, Ohio and an MBA from Cleveland State University.
Mr. Jesser serves on the board for Availity, LLC, a company that provides connectivity between health care payers and providers and is chairman of the board of National TeleHealth Network (NTN), a physician management company founded as a joint venture between American Well and WellPoint. He serves as the youth director at Our Lady of the Cedars Maronite Catholic Church in Fairlawn, Ohio.
Currently, Mr. Jesser lives in Brecksville, Ohio, with his wife, Erin, and five children.






