Our Story
History Leadership Board Careers 






Our Story
Pursuant was founded with a single goal: to help nonprofits reach more donors and raise more money.
Today, we do that by liberating nonprofit leaders through actionable data, marketing automation, and productivity tools that empower them to reach more donors and raise more dollars.
Using our intelligent fundraising process, we work with nonprofits to discover solutions for their most challenging obstacles, develop a customized framework to achieve their unique goals, implement campaigns that leverage our comprehensive services, and review results to make an even greater impact in the future.
Your mission is important, but the challenges have never been greater. We want to help you work smarter, not harder.








History
We are grateful to have served institutions and nonprofits for decades. Here’s a brief look into our incredible journey from passionate startup to one of the world’s only comprehensive fundraising agencies:



2001Pursuant was founded in a loft in Dallas by Matt Frazier. Over the next few years, our growing staff moved out of the loft, serving hundreds of clients predominantly through online solutions.
2007Pursuant acquired Charitable Partners in 2008 – augmenting our annual fund solutions with a revolutionary donor upgrade model that delivered incredible results.
2009Pursuant acquired Viscern, a holding company for RSI Stewardship and Ketchum, adding a combined 127 years of experience in campaign services to our organization. The acquisition allowed us enhance the timeless principles of fundraising with innovative solutions.
2010Pursuant acquired KMA Communications whose direct response fundraising and data analytics allowed us to help nonprofits reach donors across every communications channel and all levels of the donor pyramid.
2013Pursuant named to Inc. 5000 Honor Roll after being ranked as one of the nation’s fastest growing private companies for five consecutive years.
2014Pursuant invests in advanced proprietary data analytics and donor lead generation systems. Hires top talent to lead ongoing development and expands team to provide world-class business intelligence services.
2015Pursuant acquired 2DIALOG, a fundraising automation software product suite for nonprofits.
2017Pursuant acquired TouchPoint Software, a cloud-based church management software system (ChMS) developed by church leaders for church leaders.
.

Today
Pursuant employs more than 100 professionals that span the entire spectrum of fundraising. Our talented staff include experienced fundraising consultants, direct response strategists, creative teams, data analysts, award-winning writers and videographers, in-house web developers, outsourced gift officers, an in-house print facility, and a management team with experience across all facets of client engagement.
The successful results and insights gleaned from our work with more than 200 unique organizations brings a high level of perspective and innovation to all of our clients.









“The successful results and insights gleaned from our work with more than 200 unique organizations brings a high level of perspective and innovation to all of our clients. ” Trent Ricker, CEO Pursuant 








