If you cannot purchase insurance, the government will charge you a fine when you file your yearly income taxes. For 2015, the fine will be either $325 or 2% of your income (the higher of the two will be your fee). This fee will increase to $695 or 2.5% of your yearly income in 2016. To avoid the penalty, you have to be carrying a health insurance plan for at least 9 months of the year.





